<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="478" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1228,2011]" lastBlockId="14.[151,1437,151,861]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="478" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1445,1471]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[324,580,1445,1471]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis box="[324,580,1445,1471]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">Ololaelaps ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the Far East of 
<collectingCountry box="[1002,1077,1445,1471]" name="Russia" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V." box="[1094,1428,1445,1472]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" pagination="61 - 87" refId="ref8032" refString="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V. (1964) Mites of the genus Ololaelaps Berlese, 1964 (Acarina: Laelaptidae). Parazitologicheskii Sbornik, 22, 61 - 87. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1964">Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964</bibRefCitation>
) where it was found on small rodents or in their nests, and has also been recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[1095,1162,1481,1507]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ren, T. - G. &amp; Guo, X. - G." box="[1177,1381,1481,1507]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" pagination="326 - 332" refId="ref9276" refString="Ren, T. - G. &amp; Guo, X. - G. (2008) Preliminary study on Laelapidae fauna in China (Acari: Gamasidna: Laelapidae). Chinese Journal of Vector Biology and Control, 19 (4), 326 - 332." type="journal article" year="2008">Ren &amp; Guo, 2008</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,196,1517,1543]" name="Iran" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">Iran</collectingCountry>
from soil-litter (
<bibRefCitation author="Nemati, A. &amp; Riahi, E. &amp; Khalili-Moghadam, A. &amp; Gwiazdowicz, D. J." box="[382,605,1517,1543]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" pagination="115 - 191" refId="ref9208" refString="Nemati, A., Riahi, E., Khalili-Moghadam, A. &amp; Gwiazdowicz, D. J. (2018) A catalogue of the Iranian Mesostigmata (Acari): additions and updates of the previous catalogue. Persian Journal of Acarology, 7, 115 - 191. https: // doi. org / 10.22073 / pja. v 7 i 2.36985" type="journal article" year="2018">
Nemati 
<emphasis box="[474,523,1517,1543]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">et al</emphasis>
., 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V." box="[624,961,1517,1544]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" pagination="61 - 87" refId="ref8032" refString="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V. (1964) Mites of the genus Ololaelaps Berlese, 1964 (Acarina: Laelaptidae). Parazitologicheskii Sbornik, 22, 61 - 87. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1964">Bregetova &amp; Koroleva (1964)</bibRefCitation>
designated 
<typeStatus box="[1095,1193,1517,1543]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">syntypes</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[1241,1399,1517,1543]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis box="[1241,1261,1517,1543]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1275,1399,1518,1543]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in this study, a 
<typeStatus box="[288,391,1553,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">lectotype</typeStatus>
is chosen among the examined 
<typeStatus box="[743,845,1553,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">syntypes</typeStatus>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[903,1006,1553,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">lectotype</typeStatus>
is necessary to stabilise the distinction betwee 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[238,397,1589,1615]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis box="[238,258,1589,1615]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[273,397,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the other species discussed here. 
<bibRefCitation author="Babaeian, E. &amp; Ghobari, H. &amp; Samani, K. M." box="[828,1080,1589,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" pagination="351 - 364" refId="ref7640" refString="Babaeian, E., Ghobari, H. &amp; Samani, K. M. (2019) Redescription of Ololaelaps tasmanicus (Womersley, 1956) and description of a new species of Ololaelaps Berlese (Acari: Laelapidae) from Iran. Zootaxa, 4629 (3), 351 - 364. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4629.3.3" type="journal article" year="2019">
Babaeian 
<emphasis box="[940,990,1589,1615]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
drew attention to the similarity between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[253,413,1625,1651]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis box="[253,273,1625,1651]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[289,413,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[471,630,1625,1651]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasicus">
<emphasis box="[471,491,1625,1651]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[507,630,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">caucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and stated that 
<bibRefCitation author="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V." box="[820,1161,1625,1652]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" pagination="61 - 87" refId="ref8032" refString="Bregetova, N. G. &amp; Koroleva, E. V. (1964) Mites of the genus Ololaelaps Berlese, 1964 (Acarina: Laelaptidae). Parazitologicheskii Sbornik, 22, 61 - 87. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1964">Bregetova &amp; Koroleva (1964)</bibRefCitation>
distinguished these two species from each other by small, weak or vague differences (e.g. mainly the reticulation of the epipleura, the ornamentation of genitiventrianal shield, and the number of hypostomal denticles). Babaeian 
<emphasis box="[1151,1201,1697,1723]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">et al</emphasis>
. believed such small morphological differences may represent intraspecific variations. In the meantime, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ma, L. - M." box="[1086,1206,1733,1760]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" pagination="95 - 98" refId="ref9018" refString="Ma, L. - M. (2016) New synonyms of Mesostigmatic mites (Acari). Acta Arachnologica Sinica, 25, 95 - 98. [in Chinese]" type="journal article" year="2016">Ma (2016)</bibRefCitation>
also considered that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[151,405,1769,1795]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis box="[151,405,1769,1795]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">Ololaelaps ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1923" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1923" box="[674,962,1769,1795]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis box="[674,694,1769,1795]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[709,798,1770,1795]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">sinensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese, A." box="[805,962,1769,1795]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" pagination="237 - 262" refId="ref7953" refString="Berlese, A. (1923) Centuria sesta di Acari nuovi. Redia, 15, 237 - 262." type="journal article" year="1923">Berlese, 1923</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ma, L. - M." box="[1090,1209,1769,1796]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" pagination="95 - 98" refId="ref9018" refString="Ma, L. - M. (2016) New synonyms of Mesostigmatic mites (Acari). Acta Arachnologica Sinica, 25, 95 - 98. [in Chinese]" type="journal article" year="2016">Ma (2016)</bibRefCitation>
did not provide any explanation for this decision, nor did he provide the details of the examined specimens. The species was originally described as 
<taxonomicName box="[296,558,1841,1867]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Laelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="venetus" variety="sinensis">
<emphasis box="[296,316,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[330,414,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">venetus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[469,558,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[626,693,1841,1867]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese, A." box="[708,866,1841,1867]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" pagination="237 - 262" refId="ref7953" refString="Berlese, A. (1923) Centuria sesta di Acari nuovi. Redia, 15, 237 - 262." type="journal article" year="1923">Berlese, 1923</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ryke, P. A. J." box="[934,1073,1841,1868]" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" pagination="124 - 130" refId="ref9326" refString="Ryke, P. A. J. (1962) The genus Ololaelaps Berlese (Acarina: Laelaptidae). Revista de Biologia, 3, 124 - 130." type="journal article" year="1962">Ryke (1962)</bibRefCitation>
raised it to the species level and provided some more information. However, they both lack most important details and the type series of this species may never have been re-examined. We also have not had the opportunity to examine the type specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1923" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis box="[1409,1429,1913,1939]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,240,1950,1975]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in order to confirm this synonymy, but at least we had the opportunity to examine the type specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[151,309,1985,2011]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis box="[151,171,1985,2011]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[185,309,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[363,520,1985,2011]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="13" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasicus">
<emphasis box="[363,383,1985,2011]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[397,520,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="477">caucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in order to compare these two species carefully. Therefore, in this study, we retain these three species as distinct species and confirm all diagnostic character states listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Beaulieu, F. &amp; Quintero-Gutierrez, E. J. &amp; Sandmann, J. &amp; Klarner, B. &amp; Widyastuti, R. &amp; Combita-Heredia, O. &amp; Scheu, S." box="[1153,1397,151,177]" pageId="14" pageNumber="478" pagination="1 - 36" refId="ref7827" refString="Beaulieu, F., Quintero-Gutierrez, E. J., Sandmann, J., Klarner, B., Widyastuti, R., Combita-Heredia, O. &amp; Scheu, S. (2019) Review of the mite genus Ololaelaps (Acari, Laelapidae) and redescription of O. formidabilis Berlese. ZooKeys, 853, 1 - 36. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 853.29407" type="journal article" year="2019">
Beaulieu 
<emphasis box="[1259,1309,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
for each, and herein provide additional clarification of characters for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[893,1052,187,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="14" pageNumber="478" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis box="[893,913,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[928,1052,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the examination of type series specimens. All these observations were made on all specimens examined, unless specified: (1) dorsal shield essentially smooth, without reticulation (i.e. not reticulate, but completely micropunctate) over whole surface except ventrolateral margins (epipleura) which are relatively well extended ventrally and lineate-reticulate, cells narrow and oriented mostly longitudinally or diagonally (but not compressed as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[1006,1129,331,356]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="14" pageNumber="478" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasicus">
<emphasis box="[1006,1129,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">caucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (see 
<figureCitation box="[1200,1331,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–47" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@12.[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 43–47. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps ussuriensis Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 43, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 44, sternal shield; 45, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 46, subcapitulum; 47, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571772/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">Figs 43, 45</figureCitation>
), bearing 39 pairs of setae (
<emphasis box="[348,373,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">Jx</emphasis>
seta absent); (2) metasternal setae 
<emphasis box="[762,795,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">st4</emphasis>
and metasternal poroids obviously inserted on the sternal shield margin (
<figureCitation box="[323,409,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–47" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@12.[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 43–47. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps ussuriensis Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 43, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 44, sternal shield; 45, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 46, subcapitulum; 47, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571772/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
), posterior margin of shield slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[938,1073,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–47" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@12.[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 43–47. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps ussuriensis Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 43, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 44, sternal shield; 45, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 46, subcapitulum; 47, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571772/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">Figs 43, 44</figureCitation>
); (3) metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield and shield ornamented by scale-like cells and bearing five pairs of pre-anal setae (
<emphasis box="[1362,1430,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">Jv1–3</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[151,221,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">Zv1–2</emphasis>
) in addition to seta 
<emphasis box="[440,473,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">st5</emphasis>
(in all examined specimens) (
<figureCitation box="[805,889,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–47" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@12.[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 43–47. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps ussuriensis Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 43, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 44, sternal shield; 45, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 46, subcapitulum; 47, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571772/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
); (4) hypostomal groove with six transverse rows of denticles, each row with 2–3 relatively large denticles, groove wider anteriorly, progressively narrowing from anterior to posterior (
<figureCitation box="[388,473,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–47" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@12.[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 43–47. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps ussuriensis Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 43, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 44, sternal shield; 45, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 46, subcapitulum; 47, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571772/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
); (5) the pretarsal paradactyli on legs II–IV relatively short, with tips barely extending beyond claws (
<figureCitation box="[323,408,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–47" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@12.[177,1411,181,1876]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 43–47. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps ussuriensis Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (lectotype), female. 43, idiosoma in ventral view, showing ornamentation of the hologastric shield; 44, sternal shield; 45, details of peritrematal shield, metapodal elements partly fused to hologastric shield, showing ornamentation of epipleuron (ventrolateral portion of dorsal shield); 46, subcapitulum; 47, tarsus IV, pretarsal paradactyli (p.p)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571772/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
); (6) insemination structures not discernible; (7) spermatodactyl short, with a straight duct and without hump subapically (
<figureCitation box="[500,583,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–51" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1122,1146]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,184,1096]" captionTargetId="figure-448@13.[151,1435,170,1111]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48–51. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps ussuriensis Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (paralectotype), male. 48, chelicera; 49, tarsus II; 50, genu II, 51, femur IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571774" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571774/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
); (8) in the male tarsus II bearing a stout spur-like ventral seta (
<emphasis box="[1277,1317,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">pv2</emphasis>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1341,1423,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–51" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1122,1146]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,184,1096]" captionTargetId="figure-448@13.[151,1435,170,1111]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48–51. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps ussuriensis Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (paralectotype), male. 48, chelicera; 49, tarsus II; 50, genu II, 51, femur IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571774" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571774/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
), genu II and femur IV with cuticular tubercles (see 
<figureCitation box="[706,852,654,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–51" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1122,1146]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,184,1096]" captionTargetId="figure-448@13.[151,1435,170,1111]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48–51. DIC micrographs of Ololaelaps ussuriensis Bregetova &amp; Koroleva, 1964 (paralectotype), male. 48, chelicera; 49, tarsus II; 50, genu II, 51, femur IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571774" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571774/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">Figs 50 &amp; 51</figureCitation>
). Supplementary measurements (n=2): (1) lengths of dorsal setae decreasing from anterior to posterior, most of podonotal setae 40–50 and opisthonotal setae 23–30; (2) sternal shield length 115–118, maximum width 189–195, between coxae II 104–107; (3) hologastric shield 400–415 long (4) sternal setae (
<emphasis box="[408,487,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">st1–st4</emphasis>
) 55–59, metasternal setae 
<emphasis box="[793,826,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">st5</emphasis>
and pre-anal setae (
<emphasis box="[1058,1129,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">JV1–3</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1145,1220,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">ZV1–2</emphasis>
) 44–54; (5) legs: I (530–540), II (435–450), III (387–397) &amp; IV (492–508). See Remarks for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bregetova &amp; Koroleva" authorityYear="1964" box="[995,1153,799,825]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Ololaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="14" pageNumber="478" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasicus">
<emphasis box="[995,1015,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1030,1153,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="478">caucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the main distinctions between the two species.
</paragraph>
